<p><b>Venezuela (Bolivarian Republic of): draft amendment 
</b></p>
<p><b>  22</b>/&#8230; <b>Amendment to draft resolution A/HRC/22/L.30 on the prevention
 of genocide 
</b></p>
<p><b>  1. Paragraph 4  
</b></p>
<p>The paragraph<i> should read</i> 
</p>
<p>4. <i>Encourages</i> Member States to build their capacity to prevent genocide 
</p>
<p>through the development of individual expertise and the creation of appropriate offices 
</p>
<p>within Governments to strengthen work on prevention; 
</p>
<p><b>  2. Paragraph 5  
</b></p>
<p>The paragraph <i>should read</i> 
</p>
<p>5. <i>Encourages</i> States to consider the appointment of focal points on prevention, 
</p>
<p>who could cooperate, exchange information and best practice between them and with 
</p>
<p>Special Adviser on the Prevention of Genocide, relevant United Nations bodies and with 
</p>
<p>regional and subregional mechanisms; 
</p>
<p><b>  3. Paragraph 20  
</b></p>
<p>The paragraph <i>should read</i> 
</p>
<p>20. <i>Takes note</i> of the provision by the Office of the Special Adviser on the 
</p>
<p>Prevention of Genocide of training and technical assistance to Member States to strengthen 
</p>
<p>early warning mechanisms for the prevention of genocide, as well as other prevention 
</p>
<p>capacities, and encourages Member States to consider requesting such assistance, if required; 
</p>
<p>    
</p>
<p>  
 * Non-Member State of the Human Rights Council. 
</p>
